goals.question: How does the fertility rate of developed countries compare to that of developing countries?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility']]
    plt.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate across all countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['life_expect', 'country']]
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['life_expect'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    ax.boxplot(data['life_expect'].groupby(data['country']).apply(list), vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='red'), flierprops=dict(marker='o', markersize=5, linestyle='none', alpha=0.5))
    ax.set_xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Country')
    ax.set_title('How does life expectancy vary across different countries?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['fertility'], label='Fertility Rate')
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'], label='Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of fertility rate and life expectancy over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['country_classification'] = data['country'].apply(lambda x: 'Developed' if x in ['United States', 'United Kingdom', 'Japan', 'Germany', 'France'] else 'Developing')
    data = data.groupby('country_classification').agg({'fertility': 'mean'}).reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['country_classification'], data['fertility'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])
    ax.axhline(y=data['fertility'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average Fertility Rate')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('How does the fertility rate of developed countries compare to that of developing countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country Classification')
    plt.ylabel('Average Fertility Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
